
Overview of noun destruction

The noun destruction has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                    
1. (8) destruction, devastation -- (the termination of something by causing so much damage to it that it cannot be repaired or no longer exists)
2. (6) destruction, demolition, wipeout -- (an event (or the result of an event) that completely destroys something)
3. end, destruction, death -- (a final state; "he came to a bad end"; "the so-called glorious experiment came to an inglorious end")
